Program: Outlook
Title: 06/07/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00hljwf
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 7 Jul 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, former child soldier Kon Kelei returns to South Sudan. He's now a lawyer and he plans to make a difference in the world's youngest nation. Also, 20 years after shocking pictures emerged of the state of Romania's orphanages, Tiberiu Rotaru explains how he has dedicated his life to helping the orphans of his local town. And Canadian teacher Carolle Bertrand talks about what happens when you're struck by lightning twice. Show less